<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-03T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-03T21:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/9–348: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-03T20:00:00-06:00">September
                                    3, 1948—8 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1061. Foreign Minister stated tonight, after expressing appreciation of
                            friendly and other implications of <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 847, August 26<note n="1" xml:id="d72fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> that Mexico is not interested in election to <gloss target="#t_UNSC1">UNSC</gloss>. He stated some restlessness has
                            become apparent on part of other Latin American states over repeated
                            occupation by larger Latin American states of important <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> posts. He added that Mexico’s principal
                            aspiration at moment is to obtain place on Economic and Social Council
                            at expiration her present term on Trusteeship Council.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>